<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,838,1648]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,991,1016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Buckler in advance of D 
<number box="[602,610,1006,1020]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
fin present, antrorse AIO spine absent, anterior AIO spines short (
<number box="[1355,1413,992,1016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="8.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="7.0">7–10</number>
% SL), P 
<number box="[223,231,1047,1061]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
fin long (
<number box="[343,416,1033,1058]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="51.0" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="47.0">47–55</number>
% SL), P 
<number box="[518,526,1047,1061]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
fin 
<number box="[572,586,1034,1058]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
st free ray long (
<number box="[765,794,1034,1058]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="33.0">33</number>
% SL), eye moderate (
<number box="[1049,1119,1034,1058]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="10.5" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="10.0">10–11</number>
% SL), snout long (
<number box="[1341,1414,1033,1058]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="18.0" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="16.0">16–20</number>
% SL), nape and breast lack scales, belly with scales, 
<number box="[753,809,1072,1096]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12</number>
short gill rakers (
<number box="[1020,1035,1072,1096]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
%SL), dark pigment on dorsum of 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,1108,1133]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[308,375,1108,1133]" captionStart="FIGURE 6 A" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,898,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,885,1912]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6 A. Lateral view of the holotype of Pterygotrigla robertsi, (photo courtesy of L. del Cerro). B. Dorsal view of the holotype of Pterygotrigla robertsi (photo courtesy of L. del Cerro)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285608/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[359,375,1108,1133]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,838,1648]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1144,1169]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Description.</emphasis>
D 
<date box="[371,437,1145,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<number box="[371,379,1158,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
VIII
</date>
, D 
<number box="[468,476,1158,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="2.0">2</number>
<number box="[483,513,1144,1168]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="12.0">12</number>
, A 
<number box="[552,582,1144,1168]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="12.0">12</number>
, P 
<number box="[609,617,1158,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
, long (
<number box="[695,768,1144,1169]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="51.0" valueMax="55.0" valueMin="47.0">47–55</number>
% SL) 
<number box="[845,915,1144,1168]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12</number>
+ 
<number box="[944,1028,1144,1168]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="6.95" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="3.9">3, 9–10</number>
bucklers along base of D 
<number box="[1313,1321,1158,1172]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
, GR 
<number box="[1380,1436,1144,1168]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12</number>
short + rudiments, llsc 
<number box="[430,503,1182,1207]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="61.0" valueMax="63.0" valueMin="59.0">59–63</number>
, nape and breast lack scales, nuchal spine strong (
<number box="[1112,1139,1183,1207]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="11.0">11</number>
% SL), no ocular spines, opercular spine short reaching to gill opening, preopercular spine short reaching to gill opening, preopercular ridge present, cleithral spine long (
<number box="[476,504,1254,1279]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="15.0">15</number>
% SL).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,838,1648]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1291,1316]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Coloration.</emphasis>
Del 
<bibRefCitation author="Cerro" box="[389,637,1291,1316]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" refString="del Cerro, L. &amp; Lloris, D. (1997) Gurnard fishes (Scorpaeniformes, Triglidae) from off New Caledonia, with descriptions of five new species. In: Seret, B. (Ed.), Resultats des Campagnes Musorstom. Vol. 17. Memoires du Musee National d'Histoire Naturel, 174, pp. 91 - 124." type="journal article" year="1997">
Cerro &amp; Lloris (
<number box="[571,630,1291,1315]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
describe the color in alcohol as follows: “general coloration yellowish, head slightly darker, ventral flanks below cleithral spine and ventral side anteriorly to the vent are shadowed. Traces of dark markings on D I fin between spines 
<number box="[711,755,1363,1388]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="3.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="1.0">1–6</number>
, pectoral fin blackish except uppermost ray and 
<number box="[1297,1311,1363,1387]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="3.0">3</number>
lowermost which are pale, free rays pale as well as other fins”. There is a dark irregular patch on the dorsum below the D 
<number box="[1390,1398,1416,1430]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
fin of the 
<typeStatus box="[225,323,1440,1465]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
(see 
<figureCitation box="[384,480,1440,1465]" captionStart="FIGURE 6 A" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1933,1955]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,898,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[151,1436,885,1912]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 6 A. Lateral view of the holotype of Pterygotrigla robertsi, (photo courtesy of L. del Cerro). B. Dorsal view of the holotype of Pterygotrigla robertsi (photo courtesy of L. del Cerro)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285608/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
Fig. 
<number box="[436,450,1440,1465]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="6.0">6</number>
A
</figureCitation>
) that is not mentioned in the original description. The Queensland specimen did not have any pigmentation on its dorsum nor was any dark pigment detected on the dorsal, anal and caudal fins. The P 
<number box="[1428,1436,1491,1505]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37" value="1.0">1</number>
fin was dusky with a light border.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,838,1648]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1551,1576]" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Distribution.</emphasis>
Coral Sea endemic, southwestern Pacific. Rare in collections; known only from Stylaster Seamount, off 
<collectingCountry box="[326,505,1587,1612]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and Marion Reef off Queensland, 
<collectingCountry box="[923,1029,1587,1612]" name="Australia" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Australia</collectingCountry>
. L. del Cerro (pers. comm.) notes another specimen from 
<collectingCountry box="[416,511,1624,1647]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
